957
01:22:52,471 --> 01:22:55,682
Follow the boy to see
if he leads you to that copy.

958
01:22:55,684 --> 01:22:57,683
The obvious downside
to that approach

959
01:22:57,685 --> 01:22:59,268
is the more time allowed

960
01:22:59,270 --> 01:23:00,644
the greater the opportunity

961
01:23:00,646 --> 01:23:02,690
for unfortunate mischief.

962
01:23:10,489 --> 01:23:12,908
I'm sure Adrian voiced
that concern.

963
01:23:14,493 --> 01:23:16,662
You are a unique talent,
Libby.

964
01:23:18,997 --> 01:23:21,624
Unfortunately..

965
01:23:21,626 --> 01:23:23,418
...I don't see a very
happy ending

966
01:23:23,420 --> 01:23:25,919
for Martin Salhi

967
01:23:25,921 --> 01:23:29,339
in either scenario
unless you tell me right now

968
01:23:29,341 --> 01:23:32,093
if there's a copy
and where I can find it.

969
01:23:32,095 --> 01:23:35,804
And then, you and I
can come to an understanding

970
01:23:35,806 --> 01:23:37,516
and you can just fade away.

971
01:23:42,021 --> 01:23:44,897
All I can tell you is
what I know.

972
01:23:44,899 --> 01:23:47,275
There's the original.

973
01:23:47,277 --> 01:23:50,861
A dozen notepads of material
written in longhand.

974
01:23:50,863 --> 01:23:53,238
There is not a single copy.

975
01:23:53,240 --> 01:23:55,868
No hard copy,
nor electronic.

976
01:23:58,662 --> 01:24:00,122
Leave Martin be.

977
01:24:01,916 --> 01:24:03,501
He is an innocent.

978
01:24:05,377 --> 01:24:06,795
Please, Rachel.

979
01:24:08,088 --> 01:24:09,673
Do with me what you will..

980
01:24:12,551 --> 01:24:13,886
